title: For Sale:  Robinson Armament M96 rifle
location: South Bay / Beach Cities, Los Angeles, California
postcontent:
WTS Excellent condition Robinson Armament M96 rifle with long picatinny rail
Comes with 1 16" barrel - gas system, bolt less than 200 rds  and another 20" barrel - unfired with new unfired gas system and bolt assembly.

CMAG and light NOT INCLUDED 
Pictured with a CA compliant non-pistol grip sleeve (removable with a tool for use in other states or with a bullet button)

This rifle, based on the Stoner 63 system is an excellent system that is a collector's item no longer in production. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robinson_Armament_M96_Expeditionary

This rifle comes with the long Picatinny rail that is removable as well as iron sights.  With the correct conversion kit, you can convert it to the Bren gun configuration for a top fed rifle.  

It accepts all AR type mags and is a novel, modular design.  Parts are rare and expensive, with less than 3500 units ever produced.  This one comes with two sets of gas systems, bolt assemblies and barrels.  One set of which is unfired and brand new.

The adjustable piston gas system is adjustable and can be dialed in for different ammo AND recoil characteristics.  A true pleasure to shoot as it has a very gentle recoil of the long stroke piston, adjustable gas AND a sweet two stage trigger.  

Although barrels are marked .223 Remington but are all chambered to accept 5.56 NATO (this is per the factory)

Cash only.  Local preferred through FFL dealer.   May trade for a .308 AR10 style, FAL, Bolt gun preferred plus cash
I may consider selling the spare barrel and parts separately but prefer to sell the entire system whole.

Stand out from the crowd, show up with a Stoner (ish) clone.  I am reasonable.  Text or call REDACTED

Insight Technologies 3rd Generation Night Vision Mum

To my eye (having had about eight night vision units over the years, this is probably a 64 lp tube and is a good quality unit. It has a bright tube.

Looking ahead on a black night with tall trees and no light, where I could not see five feet in front of me, I could see easily down the winding dirt road (probably 100 yards before it turned) and clearly see deep in the forest on each side into the shadows. This has a handful of dots  (5 or so) which are normal blemishes (visible as dots which are part of the normal manufacturing process and 2 thin hair marks, dust, or debris.
